<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">The laws of robotics were literally designed to cause conflict and facilitate strife in a fictional setting--I certainly hope no real goddamn system is built like that,.<p>&gt; To ensure robots behave safely, Gemini Robotics uses a multi-layered approach. &quot;With the full Gemini Robotics, you are connecting to a model that is reasoning about what is safe to do, period,&quot; says Parada. &quot;And then you have it talk to a VLA that actually produces options, and then that VLA calls a low-level controller, which typically has safety critical components, like how much force you can move or how fast you can move this arm.&quot;</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44367273&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44366409%2344367273" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
